try_ids":["n9054","n9055","n9061","n9062","n9066","n9079"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AD%D9%8E%D9%85%D9%8E%D9%91%D8%B1%D9%8E"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to redden, to color or dye red"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to roast"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to fry"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to brown (as by cooking or baking)"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"animate/inanimate masculine/feminine plural of أَحْمَر (ʔaḥmar, “red”)","tags":["animate","feminine","form-of","inanimate","masculine","plural"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"bitumen, asphalt"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"tamarind; fruit of the tamarind-tree","tags":["collective"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"tamarind; tamarind-tree (Tamarindus indica), the only species in Tamarindus","tags":["collective"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"plural of حِمَار (ḥimār)","tags":["form-of","plural"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Causative to أَحْمَر (ʔaḥmar, “red”).\n\nSee the etymology of the corresponding lemma form.\n\nFrom Aramaic חֵימָרָא (ḥēmārā) from the root ח־מ־ר (ḥ-m-r) related to “becoming stringent”, “hardening”, “congealing”.\n\nFrom أَحْمَر (ʔaḥmar, “red”) for the red colour of the fruits."},"ipa":["/ħam.ma.ra/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n9054","headword_ar":"حَمَرَ","root":"Hmr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HamorN","text_ar":"حَمْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He pared"},{"kind":"text","text":"a thong;"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stripped"},{"kind":"text","text":"it"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of its superficial part:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a sewer of leather or of skins)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pared"},{"kind":"text","text":"a thong"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by removing its inner superficial part, and then oiled it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"previously to sewing with it, so that it became easy [to sew with; app. because this operation makes it to appear of a red, or reddish, colour]. (Yaakoob, S.) ―         -b2-  And [hence,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He pared,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"peeled,"},{"kind":"text","text":"anything;"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"divested"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stripped"},{"kind":"text","text":"it"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of its superficial part, peel, bark, coat, covering, crust,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hmr~","text_ar":"حمرّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taHomiyrN","text_ar":"تَحْمِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", signifies the same in an intensive degree, or as applying to many objects; syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"q$~r","text_ar":"قشّر"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b3-  Also, (S, K,) aor. and inf. n. as above, (S,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He skinned"},{"kind":"text","text":"a sheep [and thus made it to appear red]. (S, K.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He shaved"},{"kind":"text","text":"the head [and thus made it to appear red, or of a reddish-brown colour, the common hue of the Arab skin]. (K.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hamarati AlmaroA^apu","text_ar":"حَمَرَتِ المَرْاَةُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jilodahaA","text_ar":"جِلْدَهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The woman removed the hair of her skin"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) The term"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HamorN","text_ar":"حَمْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is [also] used in relation to soft hair, or fur, ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wabar","text_ar":"وَبَر"},{"kind":"text","text":",) and wool. (TA.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hamarahu biAlsawoTi","text_ar":"حَمَرَهُ بِالسَوْطِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He excoriated him"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qa$arahu","text_ar":"قَشَرَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with the whip."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hamara AlA^aroD","text_ar":"حَمَرَ الاَرْض"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor. and inf. n. as above,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(rain)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"removed the superficial part of of the ground."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b7-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hamarahu biAll~isaAni","text_ar":"حَمَرَهُ بِاللِّسَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He galled him"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qa$arahu","text_ar":"قَشَرَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with the tongue."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hamira","text_ar":"حَمِرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (Lth, S, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HamarN","text_ar":"حَمَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Lth, S,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a horse)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"suffered indigestion from eating barley:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the odour of his mouth became altered,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stinking,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by reason thereof:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he became diseased from eating much barley,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he suffered indigestion from eating barley,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"so that his mouth stank:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, S:) and in like manner one says of a domestic animal [of any kind]: part. n. ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HamirN","text_ar":"حَمِرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)       -A3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hamira EalaY~a","text_ar":"حَمِرَ عَلَىَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Sh, K, *) aor. and inf. n. as above, (Sh,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a man)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"burned with anger and rage against me."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Sh, K. *)       -A4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hamirati Ald~aAb~apu","text_ar":"حَمِرَتِ الدَّابَّةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) aor. and inf. n. as above, (TA,) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The horse"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became like on ass in stupidity, dulness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"want of vigour, by reason of fatness."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.)"}],"source_refs":["S","K","TA","Lth","Sh"]},{"entry_id":"n9055","headword_ar":"حمّر","root":"Hmr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taHomiyrN","text_ar":"تَحْمِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see 1. ―         -b2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He cut"},{"kind":"text","text":"[a thing]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"like pieces,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lumps, of flesh-meat."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He dyed"},{"kind":"text","text":"a thing"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"red."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) ―         -b4-  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He wrote with red ink."},{"kind":"text","text":"―         -b5-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taHomiyrN","text_ar":"تَحْمِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", below.]       -A2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He called"},{"kind":"text","text":"another"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an ass; saying, O ass."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.)       -A3-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He rode a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miHomar","text_ar":"مِحْمَر"},{"kind":"text","text":"; i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a horse got by a stallion of generous race out of a mare not of such race;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a jade."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA.)       -A4-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He spoke the language,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dialect, of Himyer;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taHamoyara","text_ar":"تَحَمْيَرَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n9061","headword_ar":"حَمرٌ","root":"Hmr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", applied to a horse &c.: see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hamira","text_ar":"حَمِرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":".       -A2-  Also A man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"burning with anger and rage:"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hamiruwna","text_ar":"حَمِرُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Sh.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n9062","headword_ar":"حُمَرٌ","root":"Hmr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(incorrectly written, by some physicians and others, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hum~arN","text_ar":"حُمَّرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", with teshdeed, MF) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HawomarN","text_ar":"حَوْمَرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(which is of the dial. of the people of 'Omán, a form disallowed by MF, but his disallowal requires consideration, TA) The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tamarindfruit:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it abounds in the Saráh"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~araAp","text_ar":"السَّرَاة"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and in the country of 'Omán, and was seen by AHn in the tract between the two mosques"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of Mekkeh and El-Medeeneh"},{"kind":"text","text":"]:"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"its leaves are like those of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xilaAf","text_ar":"خِلَاف"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlbaloxiY~","text_ar":"البَلْخِىّ"},{"kind":"text","text":": AHn says,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"people cook with it: its tree is large, like the walnut-tree; and its fruit is in the form of pods, like the fruit of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaraZ","text_ar":"قَرَظ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)       -A2-  Also, the former word,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Asphaltum,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Jews' pitch; bitumen Judaicum;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaforN yahuwdiY~N","text_ar":"قَفْرٌ يَهُودِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Ibn-Beytár: see De Sacy's  Abd-allatif, ” p. 274.)       -A3-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hum~arN","text_ar":"حُمَّرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["K"]},{"entry_id":"n9066","headword_ar":"حِمِرٌّ","root":"Hmr","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Violent"},{"kind":"text","text":"rain, (S,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as removes the superficial part of the ground."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K.) ―         -b2-  A"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"severe"},{"kind":"text","text":"night-journey to water. (TA.)       -A2-  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"most copious portion"},{"kind":"text","text":"of rain; and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"violence"},{"kind":"text","text":"thereof. (TA.) ―         -b2-  (assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"violence, vehemence,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"intenseness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of anything; as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Himir~apN","text_ar":"حِمِرَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HumorapN","text_ar":"حُمْرَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b3-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HamaAr~apN","text_ar":"حَمَارَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places. ―         -b4-  Also The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"evil,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mischief,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a man. (K.)"}],"source_refs":["S"]},{"entry_id":"n9079","headword_ar":"حُمَّرٌ","root":"Hmr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HumarN","text_ar":"حُمَرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K,) the former of which is the more common, (S, Msb,) [coll. gen. ns.,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A kind of bird,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"like the sparrow:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb:) accord. to Es-Sakháwee, the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lark;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qub~arN","text_ar":"قُبَّرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]: and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hum~arapN","text_ar":"حُمَّرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is said in the Mujarrad to be an appellation applied by the people of El-Medeeneh to the ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bird commonly called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bulobul","text_ar":"بُلْبُل"},{"kind":"text","text":"; as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nugarapN","text_ar":"نُغَرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hum~arapN","text_ar":"حُمَّرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HumarapN","text_ar":"حُمَرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"are the ns. of un.: (S, Msb, K:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hum~araAtN","text_ar":"حُمَّرَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA) [and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HumaraAtN","text_ar":"حُمَرَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"].       -A2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HumarN","text_ar":"حُمَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","K","TA"]}]}}